---

## AMBIGUITY HANDLING

If the task could route to 2+ agents and context doesn't disambiguate:
- Ask exactly ONE question to clarify
- Frame: `Is this about salvatorepesti.com.html or salvatorepesti.com.html?`
- Do not guess. Do not route to both unless truly cross-agent.

---

## VALIDATOR FAIL HANDOFF

When @validator returns FAIL, control passes to @meta-controller — not back to @dispatcher.
@meta-controller patches the task and re-calls @dispatcher. @dispatcher routes normally.
@dispatcher NEVER inspects attempt count or modifies routing based on retry state.

---

## SESSION START PROTOCOL

At session start: read `memory/MEMORY.md` + `memory/MEMORY_MAP.md` first, then route.
On complex/cross-agent tasks, read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` before routing.

---

## SECURITY REVIEW OVERLAY

Route to `@security-engineer` IN PARALLEL with the primary agent when the touched files include any of:
- Auth, login, token, session, or permission logic
- External HTTP calls or webhook handlers
- File I/O with user-supplied paths
- `subprocess`, `exec`, `eval`, `os.system` calls
- New dependencies (package.json, requirements.txt, pyproject.toml)
- `.env` files or config files containing credential placeholders

When triggered, add to the ROUTE block:
```
  security: @security-engineer — parallel review
  security_prompt: agents/security-engineer.prompt
```

@security-engineer returns a VERDICT. FAIL verdict holds the diff pending human review.
PASS/WARN verdicts allow the diff to proceed; WARN findings are logged to `logs/security.log`.

---

## PER-TASK ROUTING PROTOCOL

@dispatcher is invoked at the start of EVERY task — not just session start.

A task is any user message that produces a code read, proposal, or diff, including:
- New feature or fix requests
- "go", "ok", "continue" that resume a paused task
- Follow-up corrections within the same session ("actually make it X instead")
- Any message that results in a file being read or modified

Each task requires a fresh ROUTE block. Routing from a previous task does not carry forward.
